  <h2>Types of appointment</h2>
  <p>We offer:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Telephone consultations</strong> — a clinician will call you at an agreed time</li>
    <li><strong>Face-to-face appointments</strong> — at Leven Health Centre</li>
    <li><strong>On-the-day appointments</strong> — for urgent same-day needs, call us from 08:00</li>
    <li><strong>NearMe video consultations</strong> — if a clinician invites you to a video appointment, you can join at <a href="https://nhsattend.vc/scoonie-medical-practice" rel="noopener noreferrer">nhsattend.vc/scoonie-medical-practice</a>. No account or app is needed — just a smartphone, tablet, or computer with a camera.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Who will I see?</h2>
  <p>Depending on your needs, you may be offered an appointment with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>GP</strong> — for complex or ongoing health concerns</li>
    <li><strong>Practice Nurse or Advanced Nurse Practitioner</strong> — for minor illness, wound care, immunisations, and health checks</li>
    <li><strong>Mental Health Nurses</strong> (Seonad or Andrew) — for mental health assessment and support; bookable directly via reception</li>
    <li><strong>Diabetic Nurse Specialists</strong> — for diabetes management and review</li>
    <li><strong>LTC Nurses</strong> — for long-term condition clinics (asthma, COPD, hypertension, and more)</li>
    <li><strong>Treatment Room Nurses / CTAC</strong> — for dressings, blood tests, minor procedures, and clinical admin</li>
    <li><strong>Phlebotomists</strong> — for blood tests</li>
    <li><strong>Practice Pharmacist</strong> — for medication queries and clinical reviews</li>
    <li><strong>First Contact Physiotherapist</strong> — for musculoskeletal problems; bookable directly without seeing a GP first</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Our reception team are trained to ask a few questions to help match you to the right clinician.</p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 not-prose">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-dark"><strong>One problem per consultation.</strong> To help us give every patient the time and attention they need, please raise one problem per appointment. If you have multiple concerns, please book a longer appointment or arrange separate appointments.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Home visits</h2>
  <p>If you are unable to come to the surgery because of illness or disability, we can arrange a home visit. Please call before 11:00 to request one. Home visits are for patients who are genuinely housebound and cannot safely travel to the surgery — they are not an alternative to attending in person.</p>
  <p>After 11:00, home visits can only be arranged for genuine emergencies.</p>

  <h2>Need help sooner?</h2>
  <p>Many conditions can be treated faster without a GP appointment. Consider:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/get-help/pharmacy-first/">Pharmacy First</a> — for UTIs, earache, sinusitis, sore throat, and more</li>
    <li><a href="/get-help/self-referral/">Self-referral services</a> — direct access to physiotherapy, mental health, and more</li>
  </ul>

